DESCRIPTION:Poetry Workshop With Laboni Islam in Toronto's High Park				\n				\n				\n				\n									Sunday\, May 24\, 2026\, 1-4PM Ages: 18+ years 								\n				\n					\n		\n				\n			\n							\n		\n					\n		\n				\n						\n					\n			\n						\n				\n									NOTE: Pre-registration is required for all our events\, hikes and workshops. We do this to ensure we don’t exceed our capacity for indoor events or the maximum limits for group sizes on High Park’s ecologically sensitive trails. Please register on our website before coming to High Park. We cannot guarantee availability of walk-in spots. If an event is at capacity\, please put yourself on our waitlist. We will notify waitlisted participants if we open up new spots or sessions for our events. Please contact us if you have any questions. 								\n				\n				\n				\n					Poetry Workshop With Laboni Islam in Toronto's High Park				\n				\n				\n				\n									Spend a spring afternoon with poetry at the Nature Centre and in High Park. We’ll read and discuss poems attuned to ecosystems\, then go on a guided nature walk\, responding to poetry prompts along the way. You’ll have the opportunity to share your writing\, give and receive feedback in a supportive environment. Experience how poetry can cultivate attention\, care\, community\, and deeper connections with the natural world of which we are a part. Price: $20Ages: 18+ yearsMeeting Location: High Park Forest School\, 375 Colborne Lodge Drive 								\n				\n				\n				\n									\n					\n						\n									Register Now\n					\n					\n				\n								\n				\n					\n		\n					\n		\n				\n						\n					\n			\n						\n				\n					Meet Your Instructor				\n				\n					\n		\n					\n		\n				\n						\n					\n			\n						\n				\n																\n															\n															\n				\n					\n		\n				\n			\n						\n				\n					Laboni Islam				\n				\n				\n				\n									Laboni Islam was born in Canada to Bangladeshi parents. She is a member of the League of Canadian Poets and author of the chapbooks Light Years (Baseline Press\, 2022) and Trimming the Wick (ignitionpress\, 2023). Laboni serves as an arts educator\, engaging the young and young at heart in gallery and community spaces. 								\n				\n				\n				\n									\n					\n						\n									Learn More\n					\n					\n				\n								\n				\n					\n		\n					\n		\n				\n						\n					\n			\n						\n				\n																														\n				\n				\n				\n																														\n				\n				\n						\n					\n			\n							\n		\n				\n			\n						\n				\n							\n							\n					\n												\n															\n								\n													\n												Date & Time\n					\n\n					Day: Sunday\, May 24\, 2026Time: 1-4PM\n				\n							\n					\n												\n															\n								\n													\n												Location\n					\n\n					This event will start at the High Park Forest School building located at 375 Colborne Lodge Drive. A number of changes were made to the travel network within High Park as part of the High Park Movement Strategy that might influence your decision to drive to High Park. In case you’re driving we strongly recommend you to park your car at the public parking lot near Grenadier Cafe. We continue to recommend using the TTC or biking as the best way to get to High Park and the Nature Centre. The Nature Centre is situated just a 5-minute walk from the High Park Subway Station. Please note\, High Park is closed to cars on the weekends. If your event is on a weekend\, you will need to park outside the park and walk in\, or take transit. Visit our How To Get Here page to learn more about planning your trips to High Park. \n				\n							\n					\n												\n															\n								\n													\n												Price\n					\n\n					General Admission (Adults): $20\n				\n							\n					\n												\n															\n								\n													\n												Ages\n					\n\n					This workshop is for adults ages 18 years and older. \n				\n							\n					\n												\n															\n								\n													\n												Accessibility\n					\n\n					Hike routes through High Park might include some uneven terrain and mild slopes. The High Park Forest School building is not yet an AODA-compliant facility. We try our best to accommodate accessibility needs on a case-by-case basis. Please reach out to us about any accessibility-related questions you might have. \n				\n							\n					\n												\n															\n								\n													\n												Dogs\, Pets and Service Animals\n					\n\n					Dogs and other pets are not permitted in our programs. However\, certified service animals\, such as registered therapy or guide dogs\, are welcome. \n				\n								\n						\n				\n				\n				\n									\n					\n						\n									Register Now\n					\n					\n				\n								\n				\n					\n		\n				\n			\n							\n		\n					\n		\n					\n		\n					\n		\n				\n					\n			\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n		\n				\n			\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n		\n					\n					\n			\n						\n				\n					Registration Policies 				\n				\n				\n				\n									Please ensure you’ve read and understood our registration policies:								\n				\n				\n				\n							\n							\n											\n													\n										General Cancellation Policy\n									\n								\n											\n													\n										Extreme Weather-Related Cancellation Policy\n									\n								\n											\n													\n										Behaviour Policy\n									\n						\n						\n				\n				\n				\n									\n					\n						\n									Read Our Registration Policies
URL:https://highparknaturecentre.com/event/sp26-birds-of-prey/
LOCATION:High Park Nature Centre\, 375 Colborne Lodge Dr\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M6R 2Z3\, Canada
CATEGORIES:Special Events
